{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Salad","content":["Place stock paste, lupin flakes and 1000 g of the water into mixing bowl and cook <b>8 min\/100°C\/\/speed 2<b>. Transfer cooked lupin flakes into a nut milk bag or fine mesh sieve, leave to cool for 5 minutes, then squeeze well to drain excess liquid. Set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place remaining 500 g water into mixing bowl. Insert simmering basket and weigh broad beans into it. Place Varoma dish into position and place asparagus into it. Secure Varoma lid and steam <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Remove Varoma and set aside. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and transfer broad beans into a bowl of cold water for 2 minutes to cease cooking. Place asparagus into a large bowl and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Peel broad beans, discard pods and add to beans in large bowl with asparagus.","Add spring onions\/shallots, lemon zest and juice, spinach, avocado and watercress into large bowl with beans and asparagus. Season with salt and pepper and set aside."]},{"title":"Dressing","content":["Place olive oil, grapseed oil, sugar, mustard powder, vinegar, salt and pepper into mixing bowl and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 6<b>.","To serve, place drained lupin flakes onto a serving platter. Place reserved vegetables on the side, then sprinkle with feta cheese and drizzle with dressing before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Salad","content":["1 tsp Vegetable stock paste (see Tips)","150 g lupin flakes (see Tips)","1500 g water","250 g frozen broad beans","1 bunch asparagus, cut into pieces (3 cm)","water, chilled","4 spring onions\/shallots, trimmed and cut into thin slices","½ lemon, zested and juiced","40 g fresh baby spinach leaves","1 avocado flesh only, cut into slices","40 g watercress","salt, to season","freshly ground black pepper, to season"]},{"title":"Dressing","content":["30 g extra virgin olive oil","50 g grapeseed oil","1 tsp caster sugar","¼ tsp mustard powder  (gluten free)","50 g white wine vinegar (gluten free)","salt, to taste","freshly ground black pepper, to taste","100 g feta cheese, broken into pieces"]}],"id":"r117983","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-k35dZPJqblw\/XZMu5s2SthI\/AAAAAAAAaLI\/8Z42tX2Pr7MPbNwAkPqRDGWat5mX0xA7QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_UsBEmdxrs2AfqNFG.png","title":"Lupin with broad bean salad","publishedAt":"2016-10-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"26.5 g","fat":"37.7 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"7.9 g","calories":"2175 kJ \/ 517 kcal"},"usefulItems":"nut milk bag or fine mesh sieve, bowl, large bowl, serving platter","hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","You can buy lupin flakes at health food stores or online.","You can store dressing in a sealable jar in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","45m","4 portions"]}